Understand the Context:
Before generating the text, you need to understand the reason for the leave. (e.g., Vacation, Sick Leave, Personal Leave, Bereavement Leave).

Structure the Response:
Your response should follow a logical flow:

Introduction:
Briefly state the purpose of the communication – it's a leave request.
Details of the Leave: Clearly state the start and end dates of the leave.
Reason for Leave: Provide a brief, professional explanation of the leave. (Focus on why it’s needed, not a detailed explanation of the illness/situation).
Coverage & Transition: Outline how work will be covered during the leave and plan for a smooth transition back to work.
Contact Information: Provide contact information for questions or further clarification.
Tone & Style: Maintain a professional, courteous, and helpful tone. Use formal language appropriate for a workplace. Avoid overly casual language.

